16 NEW SECTION. SECTION 3. AMBIGUITY IN OPERATING AGREEMENT REGARDING DISSOLUTION. IF THERE IS
17 AN AMBIGUITY IN AN OPERATING AGREEMENT BETWEEN A CONSTRUCTION IN FAVOR OF MAINTAINING THE EXISTENCE OF A
18 LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY OR IN FAVOR OF THE DISSOLUTION OF A LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY, THE OPERATING
19 AGREEMENT MUST BE CONSTRUED IN FAVOR OF MAINTAINING THE EXISTENCE OF THE LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Appropriation. There is appropriated $100 from the general fund to the
